{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}} '''Platform virtualization software''', specifically [[emulator]]s and [[hypervisor]]s, are [[application software|software packages]] that emulate the whole physical computer machine, often providing multiple [[virtual machine]]s on one physical platform. The table below compares basic information about [[Hardware virtualization|platform virtualization]] hypervisors.
